President Trump met with House Speaker-designate Nancy Pelosi and Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer in the Oval Office to discuss several issues, including criminal justice reform, the farm bill, and border security. The President emphasized the importance of border security and the need for a wall, while Pelosi and Schumer argued for alternative solutions to border security. The discussion became heated at times, with each side asserting their positions. The President also mentioned the search for a new Chief of Staff, stating that there were many candidates interested in the position.